==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''lai'''
# A lai was a song form composed in northern Europe, mainly France and Germany, from the 13th to the late 14th century.
# A [[poetic form]] consisting of two or more three line [[unit]]s in each [[stanza]], in the form aabaab... and continuing on in that pattern.  The third line in each unit consists of two [[syllable]]s only.
#: ''A tricky form, the [[lai]],
#: ''as it changes as it goes by,
#: ''you see.
#: ''Stanzas change form, and I,
#: ''get confused when e'er it I try,
#: ''to read.

